values.description: A document reporting the security status and related information of a means of transport.

values.name: halalSlaughteringCertificate
values.description: A certificate verifying that meat has been produced from slaughter in accordance with Islamic laws and practices.

values.name: forwardingInstructions
values.description: Document/message issued to a freight forwarder, giving instructions regarding the action to be taken by the forwarder for the forwarding of goods described therein.

values.name: forwardersAdviceToImportAgent
values.description: Document/message issued by a freight forwarder in an exporting country advising his counterpart in an importing country about the forwarding of goods described therein.

values.name: forwardersAdviceToExporter
values.description: Document/message issued by a freight forwarder informing an exporter of the action taken in fulfillment of instructions received.

values.name: forwardersInvoice
values.description: Invoice issued by a freight forwarder specifying services rendered and costs incurred and claiming payment therefore.

values.name: forwardersCertificateOfReceipt
values.description: Non-negotiable document issued by a forwarder to certify that he has assumed control of a specified consignment, with irrevocable instructions to send it to the consignee indicated in the document or to hold it at his disposal. E.g. FIATA-FCR.

values.name: heatTreatmentCertificate
values.description: A certificate verifying the heat treatment of the product is in conformance with international standards to ensure the product’s healthiness and/or shows the mode of heat treatment indicating the temperature and the amount of time the product or raw material used in the product was treated (such as milk).

values.name: conventionOnInternationalTradeInEndangeredSpeciesOfWildFaunaAndFloracitesCertificate
values.description: A certificate used in the trade of endangered species in accordance with the CITES convention.

values.name: freeSaleCertificateInTheCountryOfOrigin
values.description: A certificate confirming that a specified product is free for sale in the country of origin.

values.name: transitLicense
values.description: Document/message issued by the competent body in accordance with transit regulations in force, by which authorization is granted to a party to move articles under customs procedure.

values.name: veterinaryQuarantineCertificate
values.description: A certification that livestock or animal products, that are either imported or entering free zones, are kept under health supervision for a time period determined by veterinary quarantine instructions.

values.name: shippingNote
values.description: (1123) Document/message provided by the shipper or his agent to the carrier, multimodal transport operator, terminal or other receiving authority, giving information about export consignments offered for transport, and providing for the necessary receipts and declarations of liability. Sometimes a multipurpose cargo handling document also fulfilling the functions of document 632, 633, 650 and 655.

values.name: forwardersWarehouseReceipt
values.description: Document/message issued by a forwarder acting as Warehouse Keeper acknowledging receipt of goods placed in a warehouse, and stating or referring to the conditions which govern the warehousing and the release of goods. The document contains detailed provisions regarding the rights of holders-by-endorsement, transfer of ownership, etc. E.g. FIATA-FWR.

values.name: goodsReceipt
values.description: Document/message to acknowledge the receipt of goods and in addition may indicate receiving conditions.

values.name: portChargesDocuments
values.description: Documents/messages specifying services rendered, storage and handling costs, demurrage and other charges due to the owner of goods described therein.

values.name: certifiedListOfIngredients
values.description: A document legalized from a competent authority that shows the components of the product (food additive, detergent, disinfectant and sanitizer).

values.name: warehouseWarrant
values.description: Negotiable receipt document, issued by a Warehouse Keeper to a person placing goods in a warehouse and conferring title to the goods stored.

values.name: healthCertificate
values.description: A document legalized from a competent authority that shows that the product has been tested microbiologically and is free from any pathogens and fit for human consumption and/or declares that the product is in compliance with sanitary and phytosanitary measures.

values.name: foodGradeCertificate
values.description: A document that shows that the product (food additive, detergent, disinfectant and sanitizer) is suitable to be used in the food industry.

values.name: certificateOfSuitabilityForTransportOfGrainsAndLegumes
values.description: Certificate of inspection for the vessel stating its readiness and suitability for transporting grains and legumes.

values.name: certificateOfRefrigeratedTransportEquipmentInspection
values.description: Inspection document shows that the container, the cooling devices and measured temperature is in good working condition.

values.name: deliveryOrder
values.description: Document/message issued by a party entitled to authorize the release of goods specified therein to a named consignee, to be retained by the custodian of the goods.

values.name: thermographicReadingReport
values.description: A report of temperature readings over a period.

values.name: certificateOfFoodItemTransportReadiness
values.description: A certificate to verify readiness of a transport or transport area such as a reservoir or hold to transport food items.

values.name: foodPackagingContactCertificate
values.description: A document legalized from a competent authority that shows that the food packaging product is safe to come into contact with food.

values.name: packagingMaterialCompositionReport
values.description: A document that shows the main structure that composes the packaging material.

values.name: exportPriceCertificate
values.description: A certification executed by the competent authority from country of exportation stating the export price of the goods.

values.name: publicPriceCertificate
values.description: A certification executed by the competent authority from country of production stating the price of the goods to the general public.

values.name: drugShelfLifeStudyReport
values.description: A document containing results from the study which determines the shelf life, namely the time period of storage at a specified condition within which a drug substance or drug product still meets its established specifications; its identity, strength, quality and purity.

values.name: certificateOfComplianceWithStandardsOfTheWorldOrganizationForAnimalHealthoie
values.description: A certification that the products have been treated in a way consistent with the standards set by the World Organization for Animal Health (OIE).

values.name: productionFacilityLicense
values.description: A license granted by a competent authority to a production facility for manufacturing specific products.

values.name: handlingOrder
values.description: Document/message issued by a cargo handling organization (port administration, terminal operator, etc.) for the removal or other handling of goods under their care.

values.name: manufacturingLicense
values.description: A license granted by a competent authority to a manufacturer for production of specific products.

values.name: lowRiskCountryFormalLetter
values.description: An official letter issued by an import authority granted to the importer of goods from a low risk country which allows the importer to place its products in the local market with certain favorable considerations.

values.name: previousCorrespondence
values.description: Correspondence previously exchanged.

values.name: declarationForRadioactiveMaterial
values.description: A declaration to be presented to the competent authority when radioactive material moves cross-border.

values.name: gatePass
values.description: Document/message authorizing goods specified therein to be brought out of a fenced-in port or terminal area.

values.name: resaleInformation
values.description: Document/message providing information on a resale.

values.name: phytosanitaryReexportCertificate
values.description: A message/document consistent with the model for re-export phytosanitary certificates of the IPPC, attesting that a consignment meets phytosanitary import requirements.

values.name: bayplanstowagePlanFull
values.description: A full bayplan containing all occupied and/or blocked stowage locations.

values.name: bayplanstowagePlanPartial
values.description: A partial bayplan. containing only a selected part of the available stowage locations.

values.name: waybill
values.description: Non-negotiable document evidencing the contract for the transport of cargo.

values.name: universalmultipurposeTransportDocument
values.description: Document/message evidencing a contract of carriage covering the movement of goods by any mode of transport, or combination of modes, for national as well as international transport, under any applicable international convention or national law and under the conditions of carriage of any carrier or transport operator undertaking or arranging the transport referred to in the document.

values.name: goodsReceiptCarriage
values.description: Document/message issued by a carrier or a carrier's agent, acknowledging receipt for carriage of goods specified therein on conditions stated or referred to in the document, enabling the carrier to issue a transport document.

values.name: houseWaybill
values.description: The document made out by an agent/consolidator which evidences the contract between the shipper and the agent/consolidator for the arrangement of carriage of goods.

values.name: masterBillOfLading
values.description: A bill of lading issued by the master of a vessel (in actuality the owner or charterer of the vessel). It could cover a number of house bills.

values.name: billOfLading
values.description: Negotiable document/message which evidences a contract of carriage by sea and the taking over or loading of goods by carrier, and by which carrier undertakes to deliver goods against surrender of the document. A provision in the document that goods are to be delivered to the order of a named person, or to order, or to bearer, constitutes such an undertaking.

values.name: billOfLadingOriginal
values.description: The original of the bill of lading issued by a transport company. When issued by the maritime industry it could signify ownership of the cargo.

values.name: billOfLadingCopy
values.description: A copy of the bill of lading issued by a transport company.

values.name: emptyContainerBill
values.description: Bill of lading indicating an empty container.

values.name: tankerBillOfLading
values.description: Document which evidences a transport of liquid bulk cargo.

values.name: seaWaybill
values.description: Non-negotiable document which evidences a contract for the carriage of goods by sea and the taking over of the goods by the carrier, and by which the carrier undertakes to deliver the goods to the consignee named in the document.

values.name: inlandWaterwayBillOfLading
values.description: Negotiable transport document made out to a named person, to order or to bearer, signed by the carrier and handed to the sender after receipt of the goods.

values.name: nonnegotiableMaritimeTransportDocumentgeneric
values.description: Non-negotiable document which evidences a contract for the carriage of goods by sea and the taking over or loading of the goods by the carrier, and by which the carrier undertakes to deliver the goods to the consignee named in the document. E.g. Sea waybill. Remark: Synonymous with "straight" or "non-negotiable Bill of lading" used in certain countries, e.g. Canada.

values.name: matesReceipt
values.description: Document/message issued by a ship's officer to acknowledge that a specified consignment has been received on board a vessel, and the apparent condition of the goods; enabling the carrier to issue a Bill of lading.

values.name: houseBillOfLading
values.description: The bill of lading issued not by the carrier but by the freight forwarder/consolidator known by the carrier.

values.name: letterOfIndemnityForNonsurrenderOfBillOfLading
values.description: Document/message issued by a commercial party or a bank of an insurance company accepting responsibility to the beneficiary of the indemnity in accordance with the terms thereof.

values.name: forwardersBillOfLading
values.description: Non-negotiable document issued by a freight forwarder evidencing a contract for the carriage of goods by sea and the taking over or loading of the goods by the freight forwarder, and by which the freight forwarder undertakes to deliver the goods to the consignee named in the document.

values.name: residencePermit
values.description: A document authorizing residence.

values.name: seamansBook
values.description: A national identity document issued to professional seamen that contains a record of their rank and service career.

values.name: generalMessage
values.description: Document/message providing agreed textual information.

values.name: railConsignmentNotegenericTerm
values.description: Transport document constituting a contract for the carriage of goods between the sender and the carrier (the railway). For international rail traffic, this document must conform to the model prescribed by the international conventions concerning carriage of goods by rail, e.g. CIM Convention, SMGS Convention.

values.name: productDataResponse
values.description: Document/message responding to a previously received Product Data document/message.

values.name: roadListsmgs
values.description: Accounting document, one copy of which is drawn up for each consignment note; it accompanies the consignment over the whole route and is a rail transport document.

values.name: escortOfficialRecognition
values.description: Document/message which gives right to the owner to exert all functions normally transferred to a guard in a train by which an escorted consignment is transported.

values.name: rechargingDocument
values.description: Fictitious transport document regarding a previous transport, enabling a carrier's agent to give to another carrier's agent (in a different country) the possibility to collect charges relating to the original transport (rail environment).

values.name: manufacturerRaisedOrder
values.description: Document/message providing details of an order which has been raised by a manufacturer.

values.name: manufacturerRaisedConsignmentOrder
values.description: Document/message providing details of a consignment order which has been raised by a manufacturer.

values.name: pricesalesCatalogueNotContainingCommercialInformation
values.description: A price/sales catalogue message containing no commercial information, such as prices, terms or conditions.

values.name: pricesalesCatalogueContainingCommercialInformation
values.description: A price/sales catalogue message containing only commercial terms or conditions data.

values.name: returnsAdvice
values.description: Document/message by means of which the buyer informs the seller about the despatch of returned goods.

values.name: roadConsignmentNote
values.description: Transport document/message which evidences a contract between a carrier and a sender for the carriage of goods by road (generic term). Remark: For international road traffic, this document must contain at least the particulars prescribed by the convention on the contract for the international carriage of goods by road (CMR).

values.name: commercialAccountSummary
values.description: A message enabling the transmission of commercial data concerning payments made and outstanding items on an account over a period of time.

values.name: announcementForReturns
values.description: A message by which a party announces to another party details of goods for return due to specified reasons (e.g. returns for repair, returns because of damage, etc).

values.name: instructionForReturns
values.description: A message by which a party informs another party whether and how goods shall be returned.

values.name: salesForecastReport
values.description: A message enabling companies to exchange or report electronically, basic sales forecast data related to products or services, including the corresponding location, time period, product identification, pricing and quantity information. It enables the recip.

values.name: salesDataReport
values.description: A message enabling companies to exchange or report electronically, basic sales data related to products or services, including the corresponding location, time period, product identification, pricing and quantity information. It enables the recipient to p.

values.name: standingInquiryOnCompleteProductInformation
values.description: A product inquiry which stands until it is cancelled. It requests not only the updates since last time, but always the complete product information of a data supplier. This means that within the standing request every time a complete download of the respe.

values.name: proofOfDelivery
values.description: A message by which a consignee provides for a carrier proof of delivery of a consignment.

values.name: cargogoodsHandlingAndMovementMessage
values.description: A message from a party to a warehouse, distribution centre, or logistics service provider identifying the handling services and where required the movement of specified goods, limited to warehouses within the jurisdiction of the distribution centre or log.

values.name: meteredServicesConsumptionReportSupportingAnInvoice
values.description: Document/message providing metered consumption details supporiting an invoice.

values.name: airWaybill
values.description: Document/message made out by or on behalf of the shipper which evidences the contract between the shipper and carrier(s) for carriage of goods over routes of the carrier(s) and which is identified by the airline prefix issuing the document plus a serial (IATA).

values.name: masterAirWaybill
values.description: Document/message made out by or on behalf of the agent/consolidator which evidences the contract between the agent/consolidator and carrier(s) for carriage of goods over routes of the carrier(s) for a consignment consisting of goods originated by more than one shipper (IATA).

values.name: meteredServicesConsumptionReport
values.description: Document/message providing metered consumption details.

values.name: substituteAirWaybill
values.description: A temporary air waybill which contains only limited information because of the absence of the original.

values.name: crewsEffectsDeclaration
values.description: Declaration to Customs regarding the personal effects of crew members aboard the conveyance; equivalent to IMO FAL 4.

values.name: passengerList
values.description: Declaration to Customs regarding passengers aboard the conveyance; equivalent to IMO FAL 6.

values.name: deliveryNoticerailTransport
values.description: Document/message created by the consignor or by the departure station, joined to the transport or sent to the consignee, giving the possibility to the consignee or the arrival station to attest the delivery of the goods. The document must be returned to the consignor or to the departure station.

values.name: payrollDeductionsAdvice
values.description: A message sent by a party (usually an employer or its representative) to a service providing organisation, to detail payroll deductions paid on behalf of its employees to the service providing organisation.

values.name: consignmentDespatchAdvice
values.description: Document/message by means of which the supplier informs the buyer about the despatch of goods ordered on consignment (goods to be delivered into stock with agreement on payment when goods are sold out of this stock).

values.name: transportEquipmentGrossMassVerificationMessage
values.description: Message containing information regarding gross mass verification of transport equipment.

values.name: despatchNotepostParcels
values.description: Document/message which, according to Article 106 of the "Agreement concerning Postal Parcels" under the UPU convention, is to accompany post parcels.

values.name: invoiceInformationForAccountingPurposes
values.description: A document / message containing accounting related information such as monetary summations, seller id and VAT information. This may not be a complete invoice according to legal requirements. For instance the line item information might be excluded.

values.name: plantPassport
values.description: Document/message issued by a competent body certifying the phytosanitary status of plants or plant products for international trade.

values.name: certificateOfSustainability
values.description: Document/message issued by a competent body certifying sustainability.

values.name: callForTender
values.description: A document/message used by a buyer to define the procurement procedure and request suppliers to participate.

values.name: invitationToTender
values.description: A document/message used by a buyer to define the procurement procedure and request specific suppliers to participate.

values.name: europeanSingleProcurementDocumentRequest
values.description: A document/message requesting a self-declaration from the supplier, providing preliminary evidence during the tendering phase.

values.name: tenderingPricesalesCatalogueRequest
values.description: A document/message requesting information regarding pricing and catalogue details for goods and/or services to be offered as part of a tender.

values.name: tender
values.description: A document/message used by a supplier to bid in a procurement procedure.

values.name: europeanSingleProcurementDocument
values.description: A document/message containing a self-declaration by the supplier, providing preliminary evidence during the tendering phase.

values.name: multimodalcombinedTransportDocumentgeneric
values.description: A transport document used when more than one mode of transportation is involved in the movement of cargo. It is a contract of carriage and receipt of the cargo for a multimodal transport. It indicates the place where the responsible transport company in the move takes responsibility for the cargo, the place where the responsibility of this transport company in the move ends and the conveyances involved.

values.name: throughBillOfLading
values.description: Bill of lading which evidences a contract of carriage from one place to another in separate stages of which at least one stage is a sea transit, and by which the issuing carrier accepts responsibility for the carriage as set forth in the through bill of lading.

values.name: tenderingPricesalesCatalogue
values.description: A document/message providing information regarding pricing and catalogue details for goods and/or services to be offered as part of a tender.

values.name: forwardersCertificateOfTransport
values.description: Negotiable document/message issued by a forwarder to certify that he has taken charge of a specified consignment for despatch and delivery in accordance with the consignor's instructions, as indicated in the document, and that he accepts responsibility for delivery of the goods to the holder of the document through the intermediary of a delivery agent of his choice. E.g. FIATA-FCT.

values.name: combinedTransportDocumentgeneric
values.description: Negotiable or non-negotiable document evidencing a contract for the performance and/or procurement of performance of combined transport of goods and bearing on its face either the heading "Negotiable combined transport document issued subject to Uniform Rules for a Combined Transport Document (ICC Brochure No. 298)" or the heading "Non-negotiable Combined Transport Document issued subject to Uniform Rules for a Combined Transport Document (ICC Brochure No. 298)".

values.name: multimodalTransportDocumentgeneric
values.description: Document/message which evidences a multimodal transport contract, the taking in charge of the goods by the multimodal transport operator, and an undertaking by him to deliver the goods in accordance with the terms of the contract. (International Convention on Multimodal Transport of Goods).

values.name: combinedTransportBillOfLadingmultimodalBillOfLading
values.description: Document which evidences a multimodal transport contract, the taking in charge of the goods by the multimodal transport operator, and an undertaking by him to deliver the goods in accordance with the terms of the contract.

values.name: acknowledgmentOfReceipt
values.description: Document/message confirming a receipt to the sending party.

values.name: civilStatusDocument
values.description: Document which confirms the civil status of a person.

values.name: adviceReport
values.description: Document reporting advice.

values.name: bookingConfirmation
values.description: Document/message issued by a carrier to confirm that space has been reserved for a consignment in means of transport.

values.name: bindingOffer
values.description: Document which is a binding offer from one party to another.

values.name: bindingCustomerAgreementForContract
values.description: Document which is a binding agreement from the customer for a contract, such as an insurance contract.

values.name: coverageConfirmationNote
values.description: Document confirming that insurance coverage is granted.

values.name: generalTermsAndConditions
values.description: Document specifying general terms and conditions.

values.name: callingForwardNotice
values.description: Instructions for release or delivery of goods.

values.name: contractClauses
values.description: Document specifying the clauses applying to a contract.

values.name: specificContractConditions
values.description: Document specifying the individual conditions or clauses applying to a specific contract.

values.name: groupInsuranceRules
values.description: Document stating the rules of a group insurance contract.

values.name: questionnaire
values.description: Document consisting of a series of questions.

values.name: freightInvoice
values.description: Document/message issued by a transport operation specifying freight costs and charges incurred for a transport operation and stating conditions of payment.

values.name: arrivalNoticegoods
values.description: Notification from the carrier to the consignee in writing, by telephone or by any other means (express letter, message, telegram, etc.) informing him that a consignment addressed to him is being or will shortly be held at his disposal at a specified point in the place of destination.

values.name: noticeOfCircumstancesPreventingDeliverygoods
values.description: Request made by the carrier to the sender, or, as the case may be, the consignee, for instructions as to the disposal of the consignment when circumstances prevent delivery and the return of the goods has not been requested by the consignor in the transport document.

values.name: noticeOfCircumstancesPreventingTransportgoods
values.description: Request made by the carrier to the sender, or, the consignee as the case may be, for instructions as to the disposal of the goods when circumstances prevent transport before departure or en route, after acceptance of the consignment concerned.

values.name: deliveryNoticegoods
values.description: Notification in writing, sent by the carrier to the sender, to inform him at his request of the actual date of delivery of the goods.

values.name: cargoManifest
values.description: Listing of goods comprising the cargo carried in a means of transport or in a transport-unit. The cargo manifest gives the commercial particulars of the goods, such as transport document numbers, consignors, consignees, shipping marks, number and kind of packages and descriptions and quantities of the goods.

values.name: freightManifest
values.description: Document/message containing the same information as a cargo manifest, and additional details on freight amounts, charges, etc.

values.name: bordereau
values.description: Document/message used in road transport, listing the cargo carried on a road vehicle, often referring to appended copies of Road consignment note.

values.name: containerManifestunitPackingList
values.description: Document/message specifying the contents of particular freight containers or other transport units, prepared by the party responsible for their loading into the container or unit.

values.name: chargesNote
values.description: Document used by the rail organization to indicate freight charges or additional charges in each case where the departure station is not able to calculate the charges for the total voyage (e.g. tariff not yet updated, part of voyage not covered by the tariff). This document must be considered as joined to the transport.

values.name: adviceOfCollection
values.description: (1030) Document that is joined to the transport or sent by separate means, giving to the departure rail organization the proof that the cash-on delivery amount has been encashed by the arrival rail organization before reimbursement of the consignor.

values.name: safetyOfShipCertificate
values.description: Document certifying a ship's safety to a specified date.

values.name: safetyOfRadioCertificate
values.description: Document certifying the safety of a ship's radio facilities to a specified date.

values.name: safetyOfEquipmentCertificate
values.description: Document certifying the safety of a ship's equipment to a specified date.

values.name: civilLiabilityForOilCertificate
values.description: Document declaring a ship owner's liability for oil propelling or carried on a vessel.

values.name: loadlineDocument
values.description: Document specifying the limit of a ship's legal submersion under various conditions.

values.name: deratDocument
values.description: Document certifying that a ship is free of rats, valid to a specified date.

values.name: maritimeDeclarationOfHealth
values.description: Document certifying the health condition on board a vessel, valid to a specified date.

values.name: certificateOfRegistry
values.description: Official certificate stating the vessel's registry.

values.name: shipsStoresDeclaration
values.description: Declaration to Customs regarding the contents of the ship's stores (equivalent to IMO FAL 3) i.e. goods intended for consumption by passengers/crew on board vessels, aircraft or trains, whether or not sold or landed; goods necessary for operation/maintenance of conveyance, including fuel/lubricants, excluding spare parts/equipment (IMO).

values.name: exportLicenceApplicationFor
values.description: Application for a permit issued by a government authority permitting exportation of a specified commodity subject to specified conditions as quantity, country of destination, etc.

values.name: exportLicence
values.description: Permit issued by a government authority permitting exportation of a specified commodity subject to specified conditions as quantity, country of destination, etc. Synonym: Embargo permit.

values.name: exchangeControlDeclarationExport
values.description: Document/message completed by an exporter/seller as a means whereby the competent body may control that the amount of foreign exchange accrued from a trade transaction is repatriated in accordance with the conditions of payment and exchange control regulations in force.

values.name: declarationOfFinalBeneficiary
values.description: Declaration document to identify the final beneficiary of an asset.

values.name: usFatcaStatement
values.description: Statement regarding the Foreign Account Tax Compliance Act (FATCA) of the United States of America.

values.name: insuredStatusReport
values.description: Document reporting (e.g. annually) to the insured the actual details of an insurance contract.

values.name: groupPensionCommitmentInformation
values.description: Information document for the group pension commitment to an individual person.

values.name: claimNotification
values.description: Document notifying a claim.

values.name: assessmentReport
values.description: Document reporting an assessment.

values.name: lossStatement
values.description: Document specifying the value of a loss.

values.name: despatchNoteModelT
values.description: European community transit declaration.

values.name: despatchNoteModelT1
values.description: Transit declaration for goods circulating under internal community transit procedures (between European Union (EU) countries).

values.name: despatchNoteModelT2
values.description: Ascertainment that the declared goods were originally produced in an European Union (EU) country.

values.name: controlDocumentT5
values.description: Control document (export declaration) used particularly in case of re-sending without use with only VAT collection, refusal, unconformity with contract etc.

values.name: resendingConsignmentNote
values.description: Rail consignment note prepared by the consignor for the facilitation of an eventual return to the origin of the goods.

values.name: despatchNoteModelT2l
values.description: Ascertainment that the declared goods were originally produced in an European Union (EU) country. May only be used for goods that are loaded on one single means of transport in one single departure point for one single delivery point.

values.name: guaranteeOfCostAcceptance
values.description: Document certifying the guarantee of the document issuer that he will pay for costs of the addressee, e.g. the costs for repairing a vehicle.

values.name: closeOfClaim
values.description: Document reporting the closing of a claim file.

values.name: refusalOfClaim
values.description: Document stating the refusal of a claim.

values.name: valuationReport
values.description: Document reporting a valuation.

values.name: goodsDeclarationForExportation
values.description: Document/message by which goods are declared for export Customs clearance, conforming to the layout key set out at Appendix I to Annex C.1 concerning outright exportation to the Kyoto convention (CCC). Within a Customs union, "for despatch" may have the same meaning as "for exportation".

values.name: claimHistoryCertificate
values.description: Document which certifies the history of claims.

values.name: accountingStatement
values.description: Document specifying an accounting statement.

values.name: cargoDeclarationdeparture
values.description: Generic term, sometimes referred to as Freight declaration, applied to the documents providing the particulars required by the Customs concerning the cargo (freight) carried by commercial means of transport (CCC).

values.name: paymentReceiptConfirmation
values.description: Document confirming the receipt of a payment.

values.name: certificateOfPaidInsurancePremium
values.description: Document certifying the payment of the insurance premium.

values.name: insuredPartyPaymentReport
values.description: Report about payments done towards an insured party.

values.name: thirdPartyPaymentReport
values.description: Report about payments done towards a third party.

values.name: directDebitAuthorisation
values.description: Document giving the addressee the right to debit from an account of the authorizing party.

values.name: physicianReport
values.description: Report issued by a medical doctor.

values.name: applicationForGoodsControlCertificate
values.description: Document/message submitted to a competent body by party requesting a Goods control certificate to be issued in accordance with national or international standards, or conforming to legislation in the importing country, or as specified in the contract.

values.name: goodsControlCertificate
values.description: Document/message issued by a competent body evidencing the quality of the goods described therein, in accordance with national or international standards, or conforming to legislation in the importing country, or as specified in the contract.

values.name: medicalCertificate
values.description: Document certifying a medical condition.

values.name: witnessReport
values.description: Document containing a report of a witness.

values.name: calculationNote
values.description: Document detailing a calculation, such as an invoice calculation or a costs calculation.

values.name: communicationFromOppositeParty
values.description: Document containing a communication from the opposite party, such as in legal action.

values.name: amicableAgreement
values.description: Document specifying an amicable agreement.

values.name: outOfCourtSettlement
values.description: Document which specifies an out of court settlement.

values.name: legalAction
values.description: Document specifying a legal action at court.

values.name: summons
values.description: Document specifying a summons to court.

values.name: applicationForPhytosanitaryCertificate
values.description: Document/message submitted to a competent body by party requesting a Phytosanitary certificate to be issued.

values.name: phytosanitaryCertificate
values.description: A message/doucment consistent with the model for certificates of the IPPC, attesting that a consignment meets phytosanitary import requirements.

values.name: sanitaryCertificate
values.description: Document/message issued by the competent authority in the exporting country evidencing that alimentary and animal products, including dead animals, are fit for human consumption, and giving details, when relevant, of controls undertaken.

values.name: veterinaryCertificate
values.description: Document/message issued by the competent authority in the exporting country evidencing that live animals or birds are not infested or infected with disease, and giving details regarding their provenance, and of vaccinations and other treatment to which they have been subjected.

values.name: courtJudgment
values.description: Document specifying a judgment of a court.

values.name: applicationForInspectionCertificate
values.description: Document/message submitted to a competent body by a party requesting an Inspection certificate to be issued in accordance with national or international standards, or conforming to legislation in the country in which it is required, or as specified in the contract.

values.name: inspectionCertificate
values.description: Document/message issued by a competent body evidencing that the goods described therein have been inspected in accordance with national or international standards, in conformity with legislation in the country in which the inspection is required, or as specified in the contract.

values.name: vehicleAboardDocument
values.description: Document which must be aboard the vehicle.

values.name: image
values.description: Document consisting of an image.

values.name: audio
values.description: Document consisting of an audio recording (e.g. a telephone conversation or alike).

values.name: certificateOfOriginApplicationFor
values.description: Document/message submitted to a competent body by an interested party requesting a Certificate of origin to be issued in accordance with relevant criteria, and on the basis of evidence of the origin of the goods.

values.name: certificateOfOrigin
values.description: Document/message identifying goods, in which the authority or body authorized to issue it certifies expressly that the goods to which the certificate relates originate in a specific country. The word "country" may include a group of countries, a region or a part of a country. This certificate may also include a declaration by the manufacturer, producer, supplier, exporter or other competent person.

values.name: declarationOfOrigin
values.description: Appropriate statement as to the origin of the goods, made in connection with their exportation by the manufacturer, producer, supplier, exporter or other competent person on the Commercial invoice or any other document relating to the goods (CCC).

values.name: regionalAppellationCertificate
values.description: Certificate drawn up in accordance with the rules laid down by an authority or approved body, certifying that the goods described therein qualify for a designation specific to the given region (e.g. champagne, port wine, Parmesan cheese).

values.name: preferenceCertificateOfOrigin
values.description: Document/message describing a certificate of origin meeting the requirements for preferential treatment.

values.name: certificateOfOriginFormGsp
values.description: Specific form of certificate of origin for goods qualifying for preferential treatment under the generalized system of preferences (includes a combined declaration of origin and certificate, form A).

values.name: video
values.description: Document consisting of a video.

values.name: introductoryLetter
values.description: A letter of introduction attached to, or accompanying another document such as an insurance policy.

values.name: dataProtectionRegulationsStatement
values.description: Document specifying the terms of data protection regulations.

values.name: exclusiveBrokerageMandate
values.description: Document expressing the mandate of a client for a service only by the mandated broker.

values.name: consularInvoice
values.description: Document/message to be prepared by an exporter in his country and presented to a diplomatic representation of the importing country for endorsement and subsequently to be presented by the importer in connection with the import of the goods described therein.

values.name: inquiryMandate
values.description: Document expressing the mandate of a client for an inquiry service by the mandated provider.

values.name: riskAnalysis
values.description: Document specifying the analysis of risks.

values.name: transportEquipmentMovementReportPartial
values.description: A partial transport equipment movement report, containing only a selected part of the movements of transport equipment for a vessel in a port.

values.name: conveyanceDeclaration
values.description: Declaration of the conveyance to a public authority.

values.name: dangerousGoodsDeclaration
values.description: (1115) Document/message issued by a consignor in accordance with applicable conventions or regulations, describing hazardous goods or materials for transport purposes, and stating that the latter have been packed and labelled in accordance with the provisions of the relevant conventions or regulations.

values.name: statisticalDocumentExport
values.description: Document/message in which an exporter provides information about exported goods required by the body responsible for the collection of international trade statistics.

values.name: intrastatDeclaration
values.description: Document/message in which a declarant provides information about goods required by the body responsible for the collection of trade statistics.

values.name: deliveryVerificationCertificate
values.description: Document/message whereby an official authority (Customs or governmental) certifies that goods have been delivered.

values.name: importLicenceApplicationFor
values.description: Document/message in which an interested party applies to the competent body for authorization to import either a limited quantity of articles subject to import restrictions, or an unlimited quantity of such articles during a limited period, and specifies the kind of articles, their origin and value, etc.

values.name: importLicence
values.description: Document/message issued by the competent body in accordance with import regulations in force, by which authorization is granted to a named party to import either a limited quantity of designated articles or an unlimited quantity of such articles during a limited period, under conditions specified in the document.

values.name: customsDeclarationWithoutCommercialDetail
values.description: CUSDEC transmission that does not include data from the commercial detail section of the message.

values.name: customsDeclarationWithCommercialAndItemDetail
values.description: CUSDEC transmission that includes data from both the commercial detail and item detail sections of the message.

values.name: customsDeclarationWithoutItemDetail
values.description: CUSDEC transmission that does not include data from the item detail section of the message.

values.name: relatedDocument
values.description: Document that has a relationship with the stated document/message.

values.name: receiptcustoms
values.description: Receipt for Customs duty/tax/fee paid.

values.name: applicationForExchangeAllocation
values.description: Document/message whereby an importer/buyer requests the competent body to allocate an amount of foreign exchange to be transferred to an exporter/seller in payment for goods.

values.name: foreignExchangePermit
values.description: Document/message issued by the competent body authorizing an importer/buyer to transfer an amount of foreign exchange to an exporter/seller in payment for goods.

values.name: exchangeControlDeclarationimport
values.description: Document/message completed by an importer/buyer as a means for the competent body to control that a trade transaction for which foreign exchange has been allocated has been executed and that money has been transferred in accordance with the conditions of payment and the exchange control regulations in force.

values.name: goodsDeclarationForImportation
values.description: Document/message by which goods are declared for import Customs clearance [sister entry of 830].

values.name: goodsDeclarationForHomeUse
values.description: Document/message by which goods are declared for import Customs clearance according to Annex B.1 (concerning clearance for home use) to the Kyoto convention (CCC).

values.name: customsImmediateReleaseDeclaration
values.description: Document/message issued by an importer notifying Customs that goods have been removed from an importing means of transport to the importer's premises under a Customs-approved arrangement for immediate release, or requesting authorization to do so.

values.name: customsDeliveryNote
values.description: Document/message whereby a Customs authority releases goods under its control to be placed at the disposal of the party concerned. Synonym: Customs release note.

values.name: cargoDeclarationarrival
values.description: Generic term, sometimes referred to as Freight declaration, applied to the documents providing the particulars required by the Customs concerning the cargo (freight) carried by commercial means of transport (CCC).

values.name: valueDeclaration
values.description: Document/message in which a declarant (importer) states the invoice or other price (e.g. selling price, price of identical goods), and specifies costs for freight, insurance and packing, etc., terms of delivery and payment, any relationship with the trading partner, etc., for the purpose of determining the Customs value of goods imported.

values.name: customsInvoice
values.description: Document/message required by the Customs in an importing country in which an exporter states the invoice or other price (e.g. selling price, price of identical goods), and specifies costs for freight, insurance and packing, etc., terms of delivery and payment, for the purpose of determining the Customs value in the importing country of goods consigned to that country.

values.name: customsDeclarationpostParcels
values.description: Document/message which, according to Article 106 of the "Agreement concerning Postal Parcels" under the UPU Convention, must accompany post parcels and in which the contents of such parcels are specified.

values.name: taxDeclarationvalueAddedTax
values.description: Document/message in which an importer states the pertinent information required by the competent body for assessment of value-added tax.

values.name: taxDeclarationgeneral
values.description: Document/message containing a general tax declaration.

values.name: taxDemand
values.description: Document/message containing the demand of tax.

values.name: embargoPermit
values.description: Document/message giving the permission to export specified goods.

values.name: goodsDeclarationForCustomsTransit
values.description: Document/message by which the sender declares goods for Customs transit according to Annex E.1 (concerning Customs transit) to the Kyoto convention (CCC).

values.name: tifForm
values.description: International Customs transit document by which the sender declares goods for carriage by rail in accordance with the provisions of the 1952 International Convention to facilitate the crossing of frontiers for goods carried by rail (TIF Convention of UIC).

values.name: tirCarnet
values.description: International Customs document (International Transit by Road), issued by a guaranteeing association approved by the Customs authorities, under the cover of which goods are carried, in most cases under Customs seal, in road vehicles and/or containers in compliance with the requirements of the Customs TIR Convention of the International Transport of Goods under cover of TIR Carnets (UN/ECE).

values.name: ecCarnet
values.description: EC customs transit document issued by EC customs authorities for transit and/or temporary user of goods within the EC.

values.name: eur1CertificateOfOrigin
values.description: Customs certificate used in preferential goods interchanges between EC countries and EC external countries.

values.name: ataCarnet
values.description: International Customs document (Admission Temporaire / Temporary Admission) which, issued under the terms of the ATA Convention (1961), incorporates an internationally valid guarantee and may be used, in lieu of national Customs documents and as security for import duties and taxes, to cover the temporary admission of goods and, where appropriate, the transit of goods. If accepted for controlling the temporary export and reimport of goods, international guarantee does not apply (CCC).

values.name: singleAdministrativeDocument
values.description: A set of documents, replacing the various (national) forms for Customs declaration within the EC, implemented on 01-01-1988.

values.name: generalResponsecustoms
values.description: General response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

values.name: documentResponsecustoms
values.description: Document response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

values.name: errorResponsecustoms
values.description: Error response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

values.name: packageResponsecustoms
values.description: Package response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

values.name: taxCalculationconfirmationResponsecustoms
values.description: Tax calculation/confirmation response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

values.name: quotaPriorAllocationCertificate
values.description: Document/message issued by the competent body for prior allocation of a quota.

values.name: wagonReport
values.description: Document which contains consignment information concerning the wagons and their lading in a case of a multiple wagon consignment.

values.name: transitConveyorDocument
values.description: Document for a course of transit used for a carrier who is neither the carrier at the beginning nor the arrival. The transit carrier can directly invoice the expenses for its part of the transport.

values.name: railConsignmentNoteForwarderCopy
values.description: Document which is a copy of the rail consignment note printed especially for the need of the forwarder.

values.name: dutySuspendedGoods
values.description: Document giving details for the carriage of excisable goods on a duty-suspended basis.

values.name: proofOfTransitDeclaration
values.description: A document providing proof that a transit declaration has been accepted.

values.name: containerTransferNote
values.description: Document for the carriage of containers. Syn: transfer note.

values.name: natoTransitDocument
values.description: Customs transit document for the carriage of shipments of the NATO armed forces under Customs supervision.

values.name: transfrontierWasteShipmentAuthorization
values.description: Document containing the authorization from the relevant authority for the international carriage of waste. Syn: Transfrontier waste shipment permit.

values.name: transfrontierWasteShipmentMovementDocument
values.description: Document certified by the carriers and the consignee to be used for the international carriage of waste.

values.name: endUseAuthorization
values.description: Document issued by Customs granting the end-use Customs procedure.

values.name: governmentContract
values.description: Document/message describing a contract with a government authority.

values.name: statisticalDocumentImport
values.description: Document/message describing an import document that is used for statistical purposes.

values.name: applicationForDocumentaryCredit
values.description: Message with application for opening of a documentary credit.

values.name: previousCustomsDocumentmessage
values.description: Indication of the previous Customs document/message concerning the same transaction.

values.name: accepted
values.description: The specified document is accepted.

values.name: accompanyingGoods
values.description: Notice that a specific document will be accompanying the goods.

values.name: conditionallyAccepted
values.description: The specified document is conditionally accepted.

values.name: toArriveBySeparateEdiMessage
values.description: Notice that a specific document/message will be transmitted via a separate EDI message.

values.name: informationOnly
values.description: Notice that the specific document or message is for information only.

values.name: toArriveByManualMeans
values.description: Notice that a specific document or message will not be sent via EDI.

values.name: toBeRaisedAndSent
values.description: Request for a specific message to be formatted and transmitted or a request for a specific document to be raised and sent.

values.name: rejected
values.description: The specified document is rejected.

values.name: toBePrinted
values.description: The document or message is to be printed.

values.name: documentCurrentlyValid
values.description: Specific document is currently valid.

values.name: documentNotAvailable
values.description: Specified document is not available.

values.name: documentExhaustedByDeclarationAndAttached
values.description: Customs declaration to which the document is related completed or exhaust the allowance stated on the document. The document is attached to the Customs declaration.

values.name: documentNotExhaustedByDeclarationAndAttached
values.description: Customs declaration to which the document is related does not complete or exhaust the allowance stated on the document . The document is not attached to the declaration but has already been lodged in the Customs station.

values.name: documentExhaustedByDeclarationAndPreviouslyLodged
values.description: Customs declaration to which the document is related completed or exhaust the allowance stated on the document. The usage of the document is complete. The document is not attached to the declaration but has already been lodged in the Customs station.

values.name: documentNotExhaustedByDeclarationAndPreviouslyLodged
values.description: Customs declaration to which the document is related does not complete or exhaust the allowance stated on the document. The document can continue to be used for future declarations until the allowance is exhausted. The document is not attached to the declaration but has already been lodged in the Customs station.

values.name: documentNotAttached
values.description: Specified document is not or cannot be attached.

values.name: documentWithTheGoods
values.description: Document not attached to the Customs declaration but is attached to the goods.

values.name: documentAttachedToBeReturnedAfterEndorsement
values.description: Specified document is attached to the Customs declaration and will be required to be returned to the declarant after Customs endorsement.

values.name: documentAppliedFor
values.description: Application has been submitted for that document.

values.name: receivedForShipment
values.description: Indicates that the document has legal validity from the date of receival of the cargo.

values.name: shippedOnBoard
values.description: Indicates that the document has legal validity from the date that cargo is loaded on board a vessel.

values.name: status0
values.description: Message is at status 0.

values.name: status1
values.description: Message is at status 1.

values.name: status2
values.description: Message is at status 2.

values.name: messageUnderDevelopment
values.description: Message is under development.

values.name: documentNotFreighted
values.description: Document not to include freight figures.

values.name: documentFreighted
values.description: Document to include freight figures.

values.name: archived
values.description: The document or message has been archived.

values.name: provisional
values.description: The document or message has no official status.

values.name: documentsEnclosedInTheFirstTransmission
values.description: The documents are enclosed in the first transmission.

values.name: documentsEnclosedInTheSecondTransmission
values.description: The documents are enclosed in the second transmission.

values.name: documentNotRequiredWaiverIssued
values.description: The document is not required, waiver of requirement has been issued.

values.name: alreadyOnFileWithReceiverOfThisMessage
values.description: The document is already on file with the party receiving the message.

values.name: retainedBySenderOfThisMessageOrBySendersAgentOrRepresentative
values.description: The document is in the possession of the sender or sender's agent or representative.

values.name: documentIncomplete
values.description: The document is incomplete.

values.name: documentPreviouslySubmitted
values.description: The document has already been submitted.

values.name: documentComplete
values.description: The document is complete.

values.name: final
values.description: The document has been finalised.

values.name: onHold
values.description: The document or message will not be processed until further release information.

values.name: petroleumTax
values.description: A tax levied on the volume of petroleum being transacted.

values.name: provisionalCountervailingDutyCash
values.description: Countervailing duty paid in cash prior to a formal finding of subsidization by Customs.

values.name: provisionalCountervailingDutyBond
values.description: Countervailing duty paid by posting a bond during an investigation period prior to a formal decision on subsidization by Customs.

values.name: tobaccoTax
values.description: A tax levied on tobacco products.

values.name: energyFee
values.description: General fee or tax for the use of energy.

values.name: coffeeTax
values.description: A tax levied specifically on coffee products.

values.name: harmonisedSalesTaxCanadian
values.description: A harmonized sales tax consisting of a goods and service tax, a Canadian provincial sales tax and, as applicable, a Quebec sales tax which is recoverable.

values.name: quebecSalesTax
values.description: A sales tax charged within the Canadian province of Quebec which is recoverable.

values.name: canadianProvincialSalesTax
values.description: A sales tax charged within Canadian provinces which is non-recoverable.

values.name: taxOnReplacementPart
values.description: A tax levied on a replacement part, where the original part is returned.

values.name: mineralOilTax
values.description: Tax that is levied specifically on products containing mineral oil.

values.name: specialTax
values.description: To indicate a special type of tax.

values.name: insuranceTax
values.description: A tax levied specifically on insurances.

values.name: antidumpingDuty
values.description: Duty applied to goods ruled to have been dumped in an import market at a price lower than that in the exporter's domestic market.

values.name: stampDutyimpostaDiBollo
values.description: Tax required in Italy, which may be fixed or graduated in various circumstances (e.g. VAT exempt documents or bank receipts).

values.name: agriculturalLevy
values.description: Levy imposed on agricultural products where there is a difference between the selling price between trading countries.

values.name: carTax
values.description: A tax that is levied on the value of the automobile.

values.name: paperConsortiumTaxitaly
values.description: Italian Paper consortium tax.

values.name: commoditySpecificTax
values.description: Tax related to a specified commodity, e.g. illuminants, salts.

values.name: customsDuty
values.description: Duties laid down in the Customs tariff, to which goods are liable on entering or leaving the Customs territory (CCC).

values.name: countervailingDuty
values.description: A duty on imported goods applied for compensate for subsidies granted to those goods in the exporting country.

values.name: environmentalTax
values.description: Tax assessed for funding or assuring environmental protection or clean-up.

values.name: exciseDuty
values.description: Customs or fiscal authorities code to identify a specific or ad valorem levy on a specific commodity, applied either domestically or at time of importation.

values.name: agriculturalExportRebate
values.description: Monetary rebate given to the seller in certain circumstances when agricultural products are exported.

values.name: federalExciseTax
values.description: Tax levied by the federal government on the manufacture of specific items.

values.name: free
values.description: No tax levied.

values.name: generalConstructionTax
values.description: General tax for construction.

values.name: goodsAndServicesTax
values.description: Tax levied on the final consumption of goods and services throughout the production and distribution chain.

values.name: illuminantsTax
values.description: Tax of illuminants.

values.name: importTax
values.description: Tax assessed on imports.

values.name: individualTax
values.description: A tax levied based on an individual's ability to pay.

values.name: businessLicenseFee
values.description: Government assessed charge for permit to do business.

values.name: localConstructionTax
values.description: Local tax for construction.

values.name: lightDuesPayable
values.description: Fee levied on a vessel to pay for port navigation lights.

values.name: localSalesTax
values.description: Assessment charges on sale of goods or services by city, borough country or other taxing authorities below state or provincial level.

values.name: lustTax
values.description: Tax imposed for clean-up of leaky underground storage tanks.

values.name: monetaryCompensatoryAmount
values.description: Levy on Common Agricultural Policy (European Union) goods used to compensate for fluctuating currencies between member states.

values.name: miscellaneousCashDeposit
values.description: Duty paid and held on deposit, by Customs, during an investigation period prior to a final decision being made on any aspect related to imported goods (except valuation) by Customs.

values.name: otherTaxes
values.description: Unspecified, miscellaneous tax charges.

values.name: provisionalDutyBond
values.description: Anti-dumping duty paid by posting a bond during an investigation period prior to a formal decision on dumping by Customs.

values.name: provisionalDutyCash
values.description: Anti-dumping duty paid in cash prior to a formal finding of dumping by Customs.

values.name: preferenceDuty
values.description: Duties laid down in the Customs tariff, to which goods are liable on entering or leaving the Customs territory falling under a preferential regime such as Generalised System of Preferences (GSP).

values.name: specialConstructionTax
values.description: Special tax for construction.

values.name: shiftedSocialSecurities
values.description: Social securities share of the invoice amount to be paid directly to the social securities collector.

values.name: stateprovincialSalesTax
values.description: All applicable sale taxes by authorities at the state or provincial level, below national level.

values.name: suspendedDuty
values.description: Duty suspended or deferred from payment.

values.name: surtax
values.description: A tax or duty applied on and in addition to existing duties and taxes.

values.name: shiftedWageTax
values.description: Wage tax share of the invoice amount to be paid directly to the tax collector(s office).

values.name: alcoholMarkTax
values.description: A tax levied based on the type of alcohol being obtained.

values.name: total
values.description: The summary amount of all taxes.

values.name: turnoverTax
values.description: Tax levied on the total sales/turnover of a corporation.

values.name: tonnageTaxes
values.description: Tax levied based on the vessel's net tonnage.

values.name: valuationDeposit
values.description: Duty paid and held on deposit, by Customs, during an investigation period prior to a formal decision on valuation of the goods being made.

values.name: valueAddedTax
values.description: A tax on domestic or imported goods applied to the value added at each stage in the production/distribution cycle.

values.name: mixedTaxRate
values.description: Code specifying that the rate is based on mixed tax.

values.name: lowerRate
values.description: Tax rate is lower than standard rate.

values.name: exemptForResale
values.description: A tax category code indicating the item is tax exempt when the item is bought for future resale.

values.name: valueAddedTaxvatNotNowDueForPayment
values.description: A code to indicate that the Value Added Tax (VAT) amount which is due on the current invoice is to be paid on receipt of a separate VAT payment request.

values.name: valueAddedTaxvatDueFromAPreviousInvoice
values.description: A code to indicate that the Value Added Tax (VAT) amount of a previous invoice is to be paid.

values.name: vatReverseCharge
values.description: Code specifying that the standard VAT rate is levied from the invoicee.

values.name: transferredvat
values.description: VAT not to be paid to the issuer of the invoice but directly to relevant tax authority.

values.name: dutyPaidBySupplier
values.description: Duty associated with shipment of goods is paid by the supplier; customer receives goods with duty paid.

values.name: valueAddedTaxvatMarginSchemeTravelAgents
values.description: Indication that the VAT margin scheme for travel agents is applied.

values.name: exemptFromTax
values.description: Code specifying that taxes are not applicable.

values.name: valueAddedTaxvatMarginSchemeSecondhandGoods
values.description: Indication that the VAT margin scheme for second-hand goods is applied.

values.name: freeExportItemTaxNotCharged
values.description: Code specifying that the item is free export and taxes are not charged.

values.name: higherRate
values.description: Code specifying a higher rate of duty or tax or fee.

values.name: valueAddedTaxvatMarginSchemeWorksOfArtMarginSchemeWorksOfArt
values.description: Indication that the VAT margin scheme for works of art is applied.

values.name: valueAddedTaxvatMarginSchemeCollectorsItemsAndAntiques
values.description: Indication that the VAT margin scheme for collector’s items and antiques is applied.

values.name: vatExemptForEeaIntracommunitySupplyOfGoodsAndServices

values.name: canaryIslandsGeneralIndirectTax

values.name: taxForProductionServicesAndImportationInCeutaAndMelilla
values.description: Impuesto sobre la Producción, los Servicios y la Importación (IPSI) is an indirect municipal tax, levied on the production, processing and import of all kinds of movable tangible property, the supply of services and the transfer of immovable property located in the cities of Ceuta and Melilla.

values.name: servicesOutsideScopeOfTax
values.description: Code specifying that taxes are not applicable to the services.

values.name: standardRate
values.description: Code specifying the standard rate.

values.name: zeroRatedGoods
values.description: Code specifying that the goods are at a zero rate.

values.name: wardBed

values.name: placeOfLoading

values.name: placeOfAcceptance
values.description: [3348] Place where the goods are taken over by the carrier.

values.name: placeOfDischarge
values.description: [3392] Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place at which goods are unloaded from the means of transport having been used for their carriage.

values.name: portOfDischarge
values.description: Port at which the goods are discharged from the vessel used for their transport.

values.name: placeOfTranshipment
values.description: [3424] Place where goods are to be or have been transferred from one means of transport to another during the course of one transport operation.

values.name: goodsItemStorageLocation
values.description: [3385] To identify the place where a goods item is located.

values.name: placeOfTransferResponsibility

values.name: placeOfTransferOfOwnership
values.description: Place where the ownership of the goods is transferred.

values.name: borderCrossingPlace
values.description: Place where goods are transported across a country border.

values.name: warehouse
values.description: [3156] Warehouse where a particular consignment is to be or has been stored.

values.name: factoryplant
values.description: Factory/plant relevant for a particular consignment.

values.name: placeOfUltimateDestinationOfGoods
values.description: Place where goods will ultimately be delivered.

values.name: termsOfSalePlace
values.description: Place of departure, shipment or destination as specified in the terms of sale agreed between the parties.

values.name: customsClearanceLocation
values.description: [3080] Place at which Customs clearance should or has taken place.

values.name: portOfRelease
values.description: Port where goods are released from Customs custody.

values.name: portOfEntry
values.description: Port where final documentation is filed for Customs Entry processing.

values.name: country
values.description: Country relevant for a particular transaction.

values.name: city
values.description: City or town relevant for a particular transaction or consignment.

values.name: countryOfOrigin
values.description: [3239] To identify the country in which the goods have been produced or manufactured, according to criteria laid down for the application of the Customs tariff or quantitative restrictions, or any measure related to trade.

values.name: countryOfDestinationOfGoods
values.description: Country to which the goods are to be delivered.

values.name: railwayStation
values.description: Name or identification of a railway station/yard relevant to a particular consignment.

values.name: countryOfSource
values.description: Country in which raw material or components were originally produced prior to manufacture or assembly in another country.

values.name: building
values.description: A building or part thereof relevant to a particular consignment or transaction.

values.name: beginningOfChargeableSection
values.description: First rail station in a predefined section of the chargeable voyage. A complete voyage may be divided in sections, even within one country, that are separately chargeable using different tariff rules (split tariffs).

values.name: baseportOfDischarge
values.description: [3356] Place at which the cargo is discharged or unloaded from a means of transport according to the transport contract. The goods may or may not be discharged from the main means of transport at this place or port.

values.name: baseportOfLoading
values.description: [3322] Place at which the cargo is loaded on a means of transport according to the transport contract. The goods may or may not be loaded on the main means of transport at this place or port.

values.name: exportationCountry
values.description: [3220] Country from which the goods were initially exported to the importing country without any commercial transaction taking place in intermediate countries. Synonym: Country whence consigned. Country of despatch: Country from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

values.name: countryOfUltimateDestination
values.description: (3216) Country known to the consignor or his agent at the time of despatch to be the final country to which the goods are to be delivered.

values.name: consignmentFinalExportationCountry
values.description: [3331] To identify the country from which goods have been or will be consigned prior to final importation.

values.name: consignmentFirstDestinationCountry
values.description: [3219] To identify the country where a consignment is off-loaded from the means of transport used for the original exportation.

values.name: countryOfProduction
values.description: Country where item has been or will be produced.

values.name: countryOfTrading
values.description: Country where item has been or will be traded.

values.name: consignmentEntryCustomsOfficeLocation
values.description: [3089] To identify the customs office at which the goods enter the customs territory of destination.

values.name: consignmentExitCustomsOfficeLocation
values.description: [3097] To identify the customs office at which the goods leave or are intended to leave the customs territory of despatch.

values.name: placeOfCustomsExamination
values.description: Place where Customs undertakes a physical inspection of goods to satisfy themselves that the goods' nature, origin, condition, quantity and value are in accordance with the particulars furnished on the goods declaration (CCC).

values.name: placeOfAuthenticationOfDocument
values.description: (3410) Place where document is signed or otherwise authenticated. Synonym: Place of issue of document.

values.name: customsOfficeOfDestinationtransit
values.description: (3086) Customs office at which a transit operation is terminated. Synonym: Customs office of transit termination.

values.name: regionOfDespatch
values.description: Region from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

values.name: regionOfDestination
values.description: Region known to the consignor or his agent at the time of despatch to be the final region to which the goods are to be delivered.

values.name: regionOfProduction
values.description: Region where item has been or will be produced.

values.name: transitCountry
values.description: [3263] Country through which a goods or passengers are routed between the country of original departure and final destination.

values.name: transitCustomsOfficeLocation
values.description: [3107] To identify the customs office which is responsible for transit formalities en-route.

values.name: countryOfInvalidTransitGuarantee
values.description: Country in which the security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is not valid.

values.name: countryOfDestinationtransit
values.description: Country at which a Customs transit operation is terminated. Synonym: Country of transit termination.

values.name: chargeAndFreightDueFrom
values.description: Place or point from which charges and freight are charged.

values.name: manufacturingDepartment
values.description: A department within the manufacturing area (e.g. lacquering, assembly).

values.name: freightChargePayableToLocation
values.description: [3102] Name of a place to which a transport charges tariff applies or where freight and other related charges are to be or have been incurred.

values.name: endOfChargeableSection
values.description: Last rail station in a predefined section of the chargeable voyage. A complete voyage may be divided in sections, even within one country, that are separately chargeable using different tariff rules (split tariffs).

values.name: placeOfPayment

values.name: fullTrackLoadingOrUnloading

values.name: placeOfLoss
values.description: To identify the location where the loss occurred.

values.name: placeOfArrival
values.description: Place at which the transport means arrives.

values.name: nextPortOfCall

values.name: oncarriagePort

values.name: subprojectLocation
values.description: A place at which works occur referring to a sub-project.

values.name: firstOptionalPlaceOfDischarge
values.description: The first optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

values.name: finalPortOrPlaceOfDischarge
values.description: Name of the seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place at which the goods (cargo) are finally (to be) unloaded from the means of transport used for their carriage according to the transport contract.

values.name: expressRailwayStation
values.description: Railway station offering express transportation services.

values.name: mixedCargoRailwayStation
values.description: Railway station offering mixed cargo transportation services .

values.name: secondOptionalPlaceOfDischarge
values.description: The second optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of shipper.

values.name: nextNondischargePortOfCall

values.name: thirdOptionalPlaceOfDischarge
values.description: The third optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

values.name: reconsolidationPoint
values.description: A place where cargo is reconsolidated.

values.name: fourthOptionalPlaceOfDischarge
values.description: The fourth optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

values.name: billOfLadingReleaseOffice

values.name: transhipmentExcludingThisPlace
values.description: Place/location where a transhipment from a means of transport to another means of transport is not authorised.

values.name: transhipmentLimitedToThisPlace
values.description: Only place/location where a transhipment from a means of transport to another means of transport is authorised.

values.name: originalPortOfLoading
values.description: (3099) The port where the goods were first loaded on a vessel.

values.name: firstPortOfCallNondischarging

values.name: firstPortOfCallDischarging
values.description: Port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially arrives from the 'last place/port of call of conveyance' and where a conveyance will be discharging cargoes.

values.name: placeportOfFirstEntry
values.description: Place or port where final documentation is filed for Customs entry processing.

values.name: placeOfDespatch
