values.name: fifthOptionalPlaceOfDischarge
values.description: The fifth optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

values.name: precarriagePort
values.description: Port of loading at which the cargo is loaded on the pre-carriage vessel used for the transport prior to the main transport.

values.name: placeOfDeliverybyOnCarriage
values.description: [3358] Place to which the goods are to be finally delivered.

values.name: transportContractPlaceOfAcceptance
values.description: Place at which the goods are taken over by the carrier according to the contract of carriage.

values.name: transportContractPlaceOfDestination
values.description: Place to which the goods are destined.

values.name: countryOfValidTransitGuarantee
values.description: Country in which the security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is valid.

values.name: placeportOfConveyanceInitialArrival

values.name: placeOfReceipt
values.description: Identification of the location at which the cargo is actually received.

values.name: placeOfRegistration
values.description: (3105) Place where the registration occurs.

values.name: specialTreatmentPlace

values.name: placeOfDocumentIssue

values.name: routing

values.name: stationOfApplicationOfAdditionalCosts

values.name: previousPortOfCall
values.description: Previous port which the vessel has called upon.

values.name: sailingDestinationArea

values.name: placeOfLodgementOfDocuments

values.name: optionalPlaceOfDischarge

values.name: placeOfEmptyEquipmentDespatch

values.name: placeOfEmptyEquipmentReturn

values.name: placeportOfWarehouseEntry

values.name: countryOfFirstSale

values.name: placeOfTransfer

values.name: placeOfDeconsolidation

values.name: placeOfConsumption

values.name: placeOfConsolidation
values.description: Place where smaller consignments of goods are grouped together into a large consignment to be transported as a larger unit.

values.name: rateCombinationPoint
values.description: [3369] Point over which sector rates are combined.

values.name: placeOfProlongationDecisionOfDeliveryDelay

values.name: customsOfficeOfDespatch

values.name: regionOfEquipmentAvailability

values.name: countryOfDespatch

values.description: Customs office from which goods are taken out of the Customs territory (CCC).

values.name: freeZoneOfExport
values.description: Foreign free zone (desc: see 1131 = 131) from which goods are exported to the country of importation.

values.name: regionOfExportdespatch
values.description: Region from which the goods were initially exported to the importing country without any commercial transaction taking place in intermediate countries. Region of despatch: region from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

values.name: placeOfCollection
values.description: Place where goods are to be or could be picked up (collected).

values.name: customsOfficeOfDeparture
values.description: Customs office at which a Customs transit operation commences (CCC).

values.name: transitGuaranteeCustomsOfficeLocation
values.description: [3111] To identify the Customs office at which a security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is lodged.

values.name: countryOfTranshipment
values.description: Country where goods are transferred under Customs control from the importing means of transport to the exporting means of transport within the area of one Customs office which is the office of both importation and exportation (CCC).

values.name: customsOfficeOfDestination
values.description: Customs office where the goods are to be cleared (CCC).

values.name: wagonloadRailwayStation

values.name: siding

values.name: lastPlaceportOfCallOfConveyance
values.description: Conveyance departed from this last foreign place/port of call to go to "Place/port of conveyance initial arrival" (87).

values.name: countryOfPreviousCustomsProcedure

values.name: customsOfficeOfRegistrationOfPreviousCustomsDeclaration
values.description: Customs office where the previous Customs declaration has been lodged.

values.name: participantSenderLocation

values.name: wageNegotiationDistrict

values.name: placeOfUltimateDestinationOfConveyance

values.name: placeOfLoadingOfEmptyEquipment

values.name: placeOfDischargeOfEmptyEquipment
values.description: Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place where empty equipment (e.g. containers) was unloaded from means of transport.

values.name: regionOfDelivery
values.description: (3246) Region to which the goods are to be finally delivered under transport contract terms (operational term).

values.name: petroleumWarehouse
values.description: Bonded petroleum warehouse or the supplier source.

values.name: placeOfEntrycustoms
values.description: Place at which the goods enter the Customs territory.

values.name: livingAnimalsCarePlace

values.name: reicingPlace

values.name: weightingPlace
values.description: Place where weight can be ascertained.

values.name: marshallingYard

values.name: stoppingStation
values.description: Station where the train must stop or is stopped for unexpected handling.

values.name: loadingDock

values.name: portConnection

values.name: placeOfExpiry

values.name: placeOfNegotiation
values.description: Place where the documentary credit is to be presented for negotiation.

values.name: claimsPayablePlace

values.name: documentaryCreditAvailableIn

values.name: forTransportationTo

values.name: loadingOnBoarddespatchtakingInChargeAtfrom

values.name: placeOfDisembarkation

values.name: physicalLocation

values.name: urgentCommercialPayment

values.name: sepaDirectDebit

values.name: promissoryNote
values.description: Payment by an unconditional promise in writing made by one person to another, signed by the maker, engaging to pay on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time a sum certain in money, to order or to bearer.

values.name: promissoryNoteSignedByTheDebtor
values.description: Payment by an unconditional promise in writing made by the debtor to another person, signed by the debtor, engaging to pay on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time a sum certain in money, to order or to bearer.

values.name: promissoryNoteSignedByTheDebtorAndEndorsedByABank

values.name: promissoryNoteSignedByTheDebtorAndEndorsedByAThirdParty
values.description: Payment by an unconditional promise in writing made by the debtor to another person, signed by the debtor and endorsed by a third party, engaging to pay on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time a sum certain in money, to order or to bearer.

values.name: promissoryNoteSignedByABank
values.description: Payment by an unconditional promise in writing made by the bank to another person, signed by the bank, engaging to pay on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time a sum certain in money, to order or to bearer.

values.name: promissoryNoteSignedByABankAndEndorsedByAnotherBank
values.description: Payment by an unconditional promise in writing made by the bank to another person, signed by the bank and endorsed by another bank, engaging to pay on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time a sum certain in money, to order or to bearer.

values.name: promissoryNoteSignedByAThirdParty
values.description: Payment by an unconditional promise in writing made by a third party to another person, signed by the third party, engaging to pay on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time a sum certain in money, to order or to bearer.

values.name: promissoryNoteSignedByAThirdPartyAndEndorsedByABank
values.description: Payment by an unconditional promise in writing made by a third party to another person, signed by the third party and endorsed by a bank, engaging to pay on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time a sum certain in money, to order or to bearer.

values.name: onlinePaymentService

values.name: freeFormatGiro

values.name: clearingBetweenPartners

values.name: mutuallyDefined
values.description: A code assigned within a code list to be used on an interim basis and as defined among trading partners until a precise code can be assigned to the code list.

values.name: directPayment

values.name: automaticClearingHouseDebitdemandAccount

values.name: bankBookTransferdebit
values.description: Current value of an asset, moved from one account to another, as it appears on the balance sheet (debit).

values.name: docCollectionVia3rdPartyWithBillOfEx

values.name: docCollectionVia3rdPartyNoBillOfEx

values.name: irrevocableDocumentaryCredit
values.description: Written undertaking by a bank to pay a seller against stipulated documents that cannot be amended or cancelled without the consent of all parties involved.

values.name: transferableIrrevocableDocumentaryCredit
values.description: Written undertaking by a bank to pay a seller against stipulated documents that cannot be amended or cancelled without the consent of all parties involved and that can be transferred by the first beneficiary to one or more beneficiaries.

values.name: confirmedIrrevocableDocumentaryCredit
values.description: Written undertaking by a bank to pay a seller against credit conform stipulated documents that cannot be amended or cancelled without the consent of all parties involved.

values.name: transferableConfirmedIrrevocableDocumentaryCredit
values.description: Written undertaking by a bank to pay a seller against credit conform stipulated documents that cannot be amended or cancelled without the consent of all parties involved and that can be transferred by the first beneficiary to one or more beneficiaries.

values.name: revocableDocumentaryCredit
values.description: Written undertaking by a bank to pay a seller against stipulated documents that can be amended or cancelled at any time.

values.name: irrevocableLetterOfCreditconfirmed
values.description: Letter of credit that cannot be cancelled or amended without agreement by all the parties involved, and carries the endorsement of both the issuing bank and its correspondent, guaranteeing payment of all drafts written against.

values.name: letterOfGuarantee
values.description: Any guarantee, bond or other payment undertaking given for the payment of money on presentation in conformity with the terms of the undertaking of a demand for payment and other documents specified.

values.name: revocableLetterOfCredit
values.description: Letter of credit that can be cancelled or amended at any time by the issuing bank.

values.name: standbyLetterOfCredit
values.description: Letter of credit which is a contingent (future) obligation of the issuing bank to make payment to the designated beneficiary if the bank's customer fails to perform as called for under the terms of a contract.

values.name: irrevocableLetterOfCreditUnconfirmed
values.description: Letter of credit that cannot be cancelled or amended before a specific date without agreement by all the parties involved, and carries no guarantee that a correspondent will honour drafts presented for payment.

values.name: cleanCollectionicc
values.description: A collection in which the seller has already sent the goods and any documents giving control of such goods directly to the buyer, and where he subsequently sends his claim for payment. This type of collection involves financial documents only.

values.name: documentaryCollectionicc
values.description: A collection in which the seller exchanges the delivery of the goods and any documents giving control of such goods for payment or upon promise of payment by acceptance of a commercial document. This type of collection involves financial and commercial documents. International Chamber of Commerce (ICC) term.

values.name: documentarySightCollectionicc
values.description: A collection in which the commercial documents are delivered against immediate payment. International Chamber of Commerce (ICC) term.

values.name: documentaryCollectionWithDateOfExpiryicc
values.description: A collection in which the commercial documents are valid for a term or until a specified date. International Chamber of Commerce (ICC) term.

values.name: documentaryCollectionBillOfExchangeAgainstAcceptance
values.description: A collection in which the bill of exchange is handed over on acceptance and the payment will take place on a future date.

values.name: documentaryCollectionBillOfExchangeAgainstPayment
values.description: A collection in which the bill of exchange is handed over when payment is obtained.

values.name: collectionSubjectToBuyersApprovalicc
values.description: The collection is subject to the buyer's approval. International Chamber of Commerce (ICC) term.

values.name: collectionByABankConsigneeForTheGoodsicc
values.description: A collection in which the bank stores the goods on its premises. International Chamber of Commerce (ICC) term.
